description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to experience what it’s like working in a PICU?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome newly qualified nurses, return to practice nurses and staff who are looking for a change within their current roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amber Ward is looking for staff nurses to join its motivated and dynamic team. Amber Ward has gone through a remarkable journey the past 12 months and we are continuing to strive for even greater success. We want you to be a part of our wonderful team. Our Hospital won National Positive Practice Award in October 2018 Team of the year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is what our staff have had to say about working on amber ward:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“I feel so lucky to work alongside such a passionate and supportive team who always go above and beyond”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;As a newly qualified nurse the preceptorship academy built my confidence&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“I am so proud to work at Langley Green Hospital with fantastic people, staff and service leaders”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the first ward in the Langley Green Hospital to have all of our staff achieve 100% in their mandatory training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that staff who feel valued by their employers and are truly engaged, provide a better outcome for our service leaders. Amber Ward will also provide the opportunity to not only enhance ones knowledge of the PICU pathway but also works alongside forensic services and the Police for our 136 suite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 12 bedded ward based within Langley Green Hospital in Crawley. Crawley is situated closely to London and Brighton and benefits from a thriving, vibrant and diverse community. Amber Ward has an experienced team and works collaboratively with other wards and services within the hospital and the wider community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your application we would love to know what attributes you would bring to our team and we love to hear about what drives the nurses of today. If you want to work somewhere where your ideas are heard and your development supported- please apply and/or contact us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers The Trust&#39;s Golden Hello for band 5 or 6 Nurses, or a Relocation package up to a maximum of £2000. (pro rata applies and subject to terms and conditions. Please see attached Protocol document).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome you to arrange a visit to Langley Green Hospital alongside your application or even give us a follow on our Twitter page: @LGH_AmberPICU&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will support you and invest in you- don&#39;t miss this exciting opportunity!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scarlett Dewbery - Matron,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opal Ward, Amber Ward and 136 Place of Safety&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07824529754&lt;/p&gt;
